../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:3:  "reason": "The next-session prompt does force CSV graph plus JSON packet execution, but the executable approval gate is not strong enough to replace the current HUMAN APPROVAL blockers. A minimal approval JSON can unlock dispatch without proving the review artifact exists, was produced by the required reviewer path, was tracked, or was recorded through the auditable approval script. Denial instructions are documented, but not enforced by the script.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:5:    "APPROVAL_GATE_REVIEW_REQUEST.md:42 says not to approve if approval can be bypassed without a tracked review artifact or if denial instructions are not explicit.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:7:    "NEXT_SESSION_PROMPT.md:53-59 documents the intended agent approval flow, including denial proof/instructions and agent_approval_gate.py recording.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:8:    "AGENT_APPROVAL_GATE.md:22-31 documents commit/PR/review/approval/denial protocol, but this is only prose.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:9:    "goal_loop.py:21-30 accepts an approval as valid when decision is approved or approve, reviewer is non-empty, and evidence is non-empty. It does not verify that evidence paths exist, are under reviews/, are tracked, contain the review decision, include fallback provenance, or correspond to the approval task.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:10:    "goal_loop.py:57-65 dispatches human_approval_required rows once load_agent_approval returns valid, so a hand-written approvals/<TASK_ID>.agent_approval.json with non-empty evidence can unlock the packet.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:11:    "agent_approval_gate.py:19 makes --instruction-on-denial optional with a default empty string, and lines 44-57 allow a denied proof to be written with an empty failure_reason. This does not enforce explicit denial instructions.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:12:    "agent_approval_gate.py:22-26 verifies that the review artifact exists when the script is used, but goal_loop.py does not require the approval record to have been generated by this script or to have a matching APPROVAL-<TASK_ID> proof record.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:13:    "status_report.json:14-32 and final_verification_report.json:112-130 show the three target tasks are currently blocked only by agent approval record paths.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:14:    "REQ-026_ENVCTL_ROLLBACK_CHECKPOINTS.json:57-67, REQ-028_ENVCTL_AGENT_CONTROL_API.json:58-68, and REQ-033_PLUGIN_HUMAN_APPROVAL.json:57-67 all remain human_approval_required=true and proof_required=true, so the replacement gate must be fail-closed."
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:17:    "Harden goal_loop.py so an approval record is valid only if the referenced review_artifact/evidence paths exist, are inside the approved reviews/proof area, and match the task_id being unlocked.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:18:    "Require a matching APPROVAL-<TASK_ID> proof record in proof_records/proof_ledger.jsonl with status completed, actor agent-approval-gate, the same reviewer/model, the same approval JSON path, and checksums for both the approval record and review artifact.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:19:    "Require approval records to include review_artifact, model, reviewed_at, summary, reviewer, decision, and evidence; reject minimal hand-written records that only contain decision/reviewer/evidence.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:20:    "For fallback review, require an explicit fallback marker in the approval/review artifact when reviewer is not Claude Opus, including why Claude Opus was unavailable.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:22:    "Update goal_loop.py to treat denied approval records as an explicit approval blocker with the denial instructions surfaced in status_report.json, not merely as a generic invalid approval reason.",
../execution-framework/reviews/GPT55_APPROVAL_REVIEW.md:23:    "Add a small validation/test command that demonstrates malformed approvals, missing review artifacts, missing approval proof, and blank denial instructions all fail closed before these three tasks can dispatch.",
