Implemented the human approval surface as a repo-relative Nu plugin patch artifact at [REQ-033 patch](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/generated/patches/REQ-033_PLUGIN_HUMAN_APPROVAL.nu_plugin.patch) with the contract and proof alongside it in [REQ-033 contract](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/generated/REQ-033_PLUGIN_HUMAN_APPROVAL.contract.json) and [REQ-033 proof](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/proof_records/REQ-033_PLUGIN_HUMAN_APPROVAL.proof.json). The patch adds `codedb envctl human approvals`, a read-only projection command that turns approval requests plus optional operation-queue rows into an `envctl_human_approval_surface` table with `mode`, `approval`, and `operation` views and derived actions for `opt_in`, `approve`, `deny`, `pause`, and `delegate`.

Verification is recorded in [REQ-033 log](/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl/envctl-db-nu-plugin-migration-automation-package/execution-framework/logs/REQ-033_PLUGIN_HUMAN_APPROVAL.log). `git apply --check` and whitespace checks passed against the real `nu_plugin` checkout, the patched temp copy passed the structural gate, and task-specific Rust unit tests were included in the patch. `cargo`/`rustc` were not available in this shell, so those tests were not executed. I also refreshed the framework status, and `generated/status_report.json` now marks `REQ-033_PLUGIN_HUMAN_APPROVAL` as `complete`, which clears that dependency for `REQ-041_TWO_REPO_INTEGRATION`.
